Modifications relative to upstream
----------------------------------

1. `programs/priority-fee-distribution/` — a port of
   `jito-priority-fee-distribution` from `anchor-lang` `0.31.1` to
   `anchor-lang` `1.0.1` for use as the cf-invariants-jito-priorityfee
   harness target. Build-system and dependency surfaces were updated:

   - Upstream `solana-program = "2.2"` is dropped from direct deps.
     anchor-lang 1.0.1 supplies the bulk of the modular solana-3.x
     interfaces transitively (`clock`, `system_instruction`, `program`,
     etc.). The `anchor_lang::solana_program` shim is brought into scope
     inside the `#[program]` module so the upstream `solana_program::*`
     call sites continue to resolve without rewrites.
   - Upstream `solana_program::hash::hashv` is replaced with
     `solana-sha256-hasher = "3"` (the modular crate that anchor-lang
     1.0.1's shim no longer re-exports). This affects the `claim`
     instruction's merkle-leaf node hash + `merkle_proof::verify`'s
     intermediate-hash chain (`as &[u8]` slice coercions added there to
     unify hashv's slice element types). Precedent: cf-invariants-jito
     `tip-distribution` port.
   - Upstream `solana_program::native_token::lamports_to_sol` (used in
     one `msg!` line inside `transfer_priority_fee_tips`'s not-live-yet
     branch) is replaced with a one-line local helper at module-root,
     `lamports as f64 / 1_000_000_000_f64`, matching the standalone
     `solana-native-token` crate's `LAMPORTS_PER_SOL = 1_000_000_000`
     definition. The helper lives outside `#[program] pub mod ...` so
     Anchor's instruction-registration macro does not see it.

   The program logic — initialize / initialize_priority_fee_distribution_account
   / update_config / upload_merkle_root / close_claim_status /
   close_priority_fee_distribution_account / claim /
   initialize_merkle_root_upload_config /
   update_merkle_root_upload_config /
   migrate_tda_merkle_root_upload_authority / transfer_priority_fee_tips
   — is preserved.

2. `programs/vote-state/` — a vendored copy of upstream's
   `jito-programs-vote-state` crate (used by the
   `initialize_priority_fee_distribution_account` instruction to
   deserialize the validator vote account's node pubkey). Identical
   port pattern as the cf-invariants-jito `vote-state` vendored crate
   (anchor-lang `=1.0.1`, `solana-sdk-ids = "3"`); 21 LOC of upstream
   source preserved unchanged.

3. `references/jito_pfd_ref/` — a clean baseline copy of the ported
   `priority-fee-distribution` + `vote-state` programs plus a Crucible
   fuzz fixture (`fuzz/jito_transfer_priority_fee_total`) authored by
   CaliperForge. The fuzz-fixture sources are CaliperForge-authored
   harness code, not upstream code.

4. `references/jito_pfd_ref_planted_transfer_increments_total/` — a
   CaliperForge-authored "planted-bug" variant of the clean reference.
   It introduces a single-site logic regression into
   `transfer_priority_fee_tips` (dropping the
   `ctx.accounts.priority_fee_distribution_account
       .increment_total_lamports_transferred(lamports)?;`
   call) so the Crucible harness can prove the corresponding invariant
   class fires (`planted >= 1` violation) while the clean reference
   holds (`clean = 0` violations). The planted modification is described
   in `README.md` and visible as a diff against
   `references/jito_pfd_ref/`.

